**Ab Initio Monte Carlo Shell Model (AI-MCSM)**: A hybrid of the shell model and quantum Monte Carlo methods, using auxiliary fields and importance sampling.
**Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT)**: A low-order perturbative expansion of the energy and wave function around a Hartree-Fock reference state.
**Ab Initio Configuration Interaction (AICI)**: A selected CI method with a focus on nuclear structure and reaction applications.
**Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT)**: A diagrammatic expansion of the energy in powers of the interaction strength, the order-by-order calculation.
**Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT)**: A systematic expansion of observables in terms of the interaction strength.
**Auxiliary Field Diffusion Monte Carlo (AFDMC)**: A quantum Monte Carlo method using auxiliary fields to reduce sign oscillations.
**Auxiliary Field Diffusion Monte Carlo (AFDMC)**: A quantum Monte Carlo method using auxiliary fields to sample the Boltzmann weight.
**Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT)**: A diagrammatic approach based on expansions of the energy around a reference state.
**Ab Initio Configuration Interaction (AICI)**: A CI-based approach using realistic interactions and a truncated Hilbert space.
**Many-Body Perturbation Theory (MBPT)**: A diagrammatic expansion for ground-state energies and other observables, with systematic inclusion of higher-order terms.
**Ab Initio Configuration Interaction (AICI) Method**: A variational approach using a symmetry-adapted basis, and configuration interaction techniques.
**Auxiliary Field Diffusion Monte Carlo (AFDMC)**: A quantum Monte Carlo method using auxiliary fields to sample the wave function.
**Ab Initio No-Core Configuration Interaction (CI)**: A configuration interaction method using a no-core approach, Hartree-Fock basis, and chiral two-nucleon forces.
**Monte Carlo Shell Model (MCShell)**: A statistical approach combining shell model techniques with Monte Carlo sampling.
